Sentencas: In this study, in situ exsolved Ni-Ba-(Ce0.9Y0.1)(0.8)Ni0.2O3-delta+Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.9 (Ni-BCYN+GDC) perovskite anode is studied for application in hydrocarbon-fueled solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrocatalytic activities of the oxidation reaction of anode in hydrogen and methane atmospheres are studied.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show that the surface-exsolved Ni nanoparticles can significantly improve the electrochemical properties of the anode.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances of the studied anode in hydrogen and methane atmospheres at 750 degrees C are as low as 0.0042 and 0.0054 Omega.cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At the same time, a 36 h short-term open-circuit voltage test under a methane atmosphere confirms that the Ni-BCYN+GDC composite anode exhibits a good carbon deposition resistance.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that the Ni-BCYN+GDC composite anode is a potential novel anode material candidate for hydrocarbon-fueled SOFC.
Titulo: In Situ Exsolved Ni-Decorated Ba(Ce0.9Y0.1)0.8Ni0.2O3-δ Perovskite as Carbon-Resistant Composite Anode for Hydrocarbon-Fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
